Henry Stanford Diltz (born September 6, 1938, in Kansas City, Missouri) is an American folk musician and photographer who has been active since the 1960s.
Diltz photographed 1960s folk-rock stars who lived in Los Angeles's Laurel Canyon.
In 1971, he and songwriter Jimmy Webb nearly died in a glider aircraft accident.
Diltz contributed all the photographs to the 1978 book California Rock, California Sound, which archived the Los Angeles music scene of the 1970s.
